commitResults.messageTitle: Update AboutUs.md to include my role and responsibilities
commitResults.messageBody: Add joelsung.md for portfolio

Events are treated as a separate list and entity from Persons.

Add event package under model.
Add Event, EventDate, EventTime, Participant, UniqueEventList
classes.
Add exceptions package under event.
Add DuplicateEventException, EventNotFoundException classes.

Add CreateCommand and CreateCommandParser classes to handle create
feature.

Storage JSON file now has 2 fields Persons and Events. Both are
arrays holding person(s) and event(s) respectively.

Add JsonAdaptedEvent and JsonAdaptedParticipant classes to read
events from storage

Events and Persons displayed as separate lists in the GUI.

Add EventCard and EventListPanel classes to handle the GUI display
of Events.
Students and Events tab added to GUI menu panel to toggle between
Persons and Events list. The lists' visibility field are toggled
to create this effect.

Add respective test classes.

Add TypicalEvents class and pseudo AddressBooks with invalid and/or
valid events for test cases to use.

Generally, most Persons methods are doubled to handle Events. Some
areas common to both Persons and Events are abstracted out, e.g.
TypicalAddressBook extracted from TypicalPersons.
Event object fields also draw parallels to Person object fields,
e.g. EventName and Name.

Add an abstract DeleteCommand class that DeleteEventCommand and
DeleteStudentCommand extends from. This works as one delete command
is used to delete both an event and student.
- If the user inputs delete with a student and event field, only
the student will be deleted.

Delete deletes students by index and event by eventname. Since it
deleted by index originally, delete finds the Person by index and
deletes it accordingly.
For event deletion, added get method in UniqueEventList to return
the Event using its name to delete after. Updated ModelManager
and AddressBook accordingly.

DeleteCommandParser parses the input and decides to create a
DeleteStudentCommand or DeleteEventCommand.

Update test cases for Delete and Create commands.

Add method that checks for these new definition of equality.

A person is considered "similar" (not same) if the two share at least one of the following: NUS NetID, email, or phone.

This prevents person with duplicate fields (that are important to be unique) from being added into NUSTracker.
